@markdroth Both comments are addressed. PTAL. 
@apolcyn confirmed this PR resolved test flakiness.
@lizan With the changes in this PR, Envoy code needs to be updated to start using the new TSI handshaker API. In particular, at the Envoy startup (or cleanup), it needs to invoke `grpc_tsi_alts_shared_resource_ref()` (or `grpc_tsi_alts_shared_resource_unref`) to add (or remove) a ref to ALTS TSI shared resources. Then, when creating a TSI handshaker, the pointer to the resource needs to be passed in. Please let me know if above changes could not be applied.
